efit of having her own office (as opposed to sharing) is at least $625.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr 5) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 DeShawn's Detailing is a service that details cars at the customers' homes or places of work. DeShawn's cost for a basic detailing package is $40, and he charges $75 for this service. For a total price of $90, DeShawn will also detail the car's engine, a service that adds an additional $20 to the total cost of the package. Should DeShawn continue to offer the engine detailing service?\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr A) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 Yes, he still makes a profit by selling the engine detailing service with the basic detailing package.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr B) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 Yes, because he will increase sales of the basic detailing package.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr C) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 Yes, but only if he raises the price of the basic detailing package.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr D) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 No, his marginal benefit is less than his marginal cost.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr E) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 More information is needed for DeShawn to make this decision.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr 6) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 Households\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr A) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 purchase final goods and services in the factor market.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr B) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 purchase resources in the factor market.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr C) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 purchase final goods and services in the product market.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr D) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 have no influence on the circular flow in a market economy.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr E) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 purchase resources in the product market.\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\par\pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0\qr 7) \pard \plain\f1\fs20\cf0 The resource income earned by those who supply ________ is c